## v1.6.0 (2026-06-20)

**Changed by:** Mnemosyne issue #284 planning (add `security/sast-scan` to the
`homeric-main-baseline` ruleset as a required status check)
**Verification:** verified-local for the prerequisite-PR premise-check technique (I ran
`gh pr view 264 --json state,mergedAt` and grepped `_required.yml` on `main`, observing the
PR is OPEN and the `sast` job is absent from `main`); **unverified** for the proposed runbook
(the ruleset PUT + read-back were NOT executed — planning only).

### What changed

- Added **Section K: Verify the issue's prerequisite-PR premise before ordering the runbook** —
  a planning-discipline / premise-falsification learning. When an issue's body asserts a
  prerequisite PR already "added"/"landed"/"introduced" a CI job that a new required-context
  depends on, that past-tense claim is a CLAIM, not ground truth. Verify the PR is actually
  merged to the default branch (`gh pr view <n> --json state,mergedAt` AND grep the file on
  `main`) BEFORE writing runbook ordering that depends on it. Gate the change on the merge.
- Added a Failed Attempts row: trusting issue #284's "PR #264 added the SAST job" premise →
  PR #264 was still OPEN (`mergedAt: null`); the context never posts; adding it as required
  would permanently brick the merge queue (Section A hazard).
- Added a description trigger (11): an issue claims a prerequisite PR already added a CI job a
  new required-context depends on — verify it is merged to the default branch first.
- Added a When-to-Use trigger mirroring the description addition.
- Added tags: premise-verification, prerequisite-pr.
- Bumped Overview Date/Verification cell to record the mixed level for Section K (premise-check
  verified-local; runbook unverified), mirroring how Section J already records its mixed level.
- Added a Verified On row for Mnemosyne issue #284 planning.

### Why

Issue #284's body asserted "PR #264 added the `security-sast-scan` CI job to
`.github/workflows/_required.yml`," and the issue asked to add `security/sast-scan` to the
`homeric-main-baseline` ruleset (id 15556487) as a required status check. Taken at face value
this reads as already-landed, so the natural runbook ordering would add the required context
immediately. Verifying the premise inverted that ordering: `gh pr view 264 --json state,mergedAt`
returned `state: OPEN, mergedAt: null`, and `grep -n "sast" .github/workflows/_required.yml` on
`main` returned nothing — the job that POSTS the `security/sast-scan` context does not exist on
the default branch yet. Per the skill's own Section A (and the "context never posts → BLOCKED
forever" Failed Attempt), adding a required status-check context whose posting job is not on
`main` permanently bricks the merge queue: every subsequent PR waits forever for a context that
is never reported. The ruleset edit MUST therefore be GATED on PR #264 actually merging first;
the issue's past-tense premise made it sound already done. A secondary sub-learning: the pinned
context name is the job `name:` field (`security/sast-scan`), not the YAML job key
(`security-sast-scan:`) — confirmed by reading PR #264's diff — but because the PR is unmerged,
that name is only as stable as the unmerged PR and could still change before merge.

